    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 8: Hippocampal neurons at 21DIV were triple stained using anti-SRPK2, anti-Piccolo and anti-Shank2 antibodies. Immunofluorescence images showed occasional overlap between all three proteins, as well as overlap between SRPK2 and Piccolo.\n\nFigure 9: biochemical fractions showed SRPK2 was present in P2 and synaptosomes, and present albeit at lower intensity in PSD fractions.\n\nAuthors conclude that \"Altogether these data suggest that SRPK1 and SPRK2 are present in synapses and that SRPK2 might modulate the self-assembly of CAST1/ERC2 within presynaptic terminals\". Note that we have not annotated SRPK1 from these data as the confocal imaging only showed SPRK2.. Experimental description: Figure 8: \"SRPK2 colocalizes with synaptic proteins in cultured hippocampal neurons. Representative images show neurites in dissociated rat hippocampal cultures\"\n\nantibody:\nmouse monoclonal anti-SRPK2 (1:1000, BD Biosciences, San Jose, CA, USA).\n\nwe selected the rat uniprot accession that was closest to the mouse swissprot/reviewed record based on protein BLAST",
